The play titled "The Brothers Size" is making its return to the Market Theatre. That is in celebration of Black History Month in February. eNCA speaks to Market Theatre's artistic director, James Ngcobo. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The play titled "The Brothers Size" is making its return to the Market Theatre. That is in celebration of Black History Month in February. READ: Market Theatre photographs misleading: spokesperson The play was written by Academy Award winner Tarell Alvin McCraney. "The Brothers Size" explores the complexities of brotherhood, devotion, and freedom.